# Deny-all build context. Everything is bind-mounted at runtime via
# docker-compose.yml, so sending it to the daemon is wasted bandwidth (~11 GB
# on full builds otherwise). Un-deny only files that a Dockerfile COPYs in.
#
# Whitelisted COPY sources:
#   IsaacDockerfile  -> CL_isaaclab_sim/requirements.txt
#   MujocoDockerfile -> core_ws/src/livox_ros_driver2 (baked-in livox build)
#   BaseDockerfile   -> unitree_sdk2_python (local SDK install)
*
!CL_isaaclab_sim
CL_isaaclab_sim/*
!CL_isaaclab_sim/requirements.txt
!core_ws
core_ws/*
!core_ws/src
core_ws/src/*
!core_ws/src/livox_ros_driver2
core_ws/src/livox_ros_driver2/.git
!unitree_sdk2_python
!unitree_sdk2_python/**
unitree_sdk2_python/.git
